# Tailwind CSS Preferences

## Use `size-*` Instead of `width-*` and `height-*`

When setting equal width and height values, always prefer the `size-*` utility class instead of using both `width-*` and `height-*` classes.

**Don't do this:**

```tsx
<View className="w-12 h-12" />
```

**Instead, do this:**

```tsx
<View className="size-12" />
```

This rule applies to all size values (e.g., `size-1`, `size-2`, `size-4`, `size-8`, `size-12`, `size-16`, `size-20`, `size-24`, `size-32`, `size-40`, `size-48`, `size-64`, `size-80`, `size-96`, and any custom size values).
